The paper deals with the problem of compressed sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of statistical mechanics to analyze the reconstruction performance is a novel approach that could also be of interest to researchers in the field of statistical inference (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of matrix ensembles, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and could also be relevant to researchers in multimedia (cs.MM) who work with compressed data.
